  <abstract>This American made M1917 helmet was issued to James McFerren Johnston. The original liner and chin strap are intact. Johnston's service number "1313972" is painted on the underside of the rim. The insignia of the 30th Div. is located on the front. Pvt. James McFerren Johnston served in the HQ Co., Ord. Corps, attached to the 114th MG Battn., 30th Div. The 30th Div. consisted of National Guard units from Tennessee and North and South Carolina and their nickname was the "Old Hickory" Division.</abstract>
